subject: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miss_Coco_Peru>
object: Clinton Leupp, conosciuto con il nome d'arte di Miss Coco Peru (New York, 27 agosto 1965), è un attore e comico statunitense, noto per le sue performance da drag queen e cabarettista. Ha partecipato ai film A Wong Foo, grazie di tutto! Julie Newmar, e Trick, inoltre è stato ospite di serie televisive come Will & Grace e Arrested Development - Ti presento i miei. Ha partecipato anche ai film e e nel 2006 ha prestato la voce a mamma Ippopotamo nel film d'animazione Uno zoo in fuga.

subject: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miss_Coco_Peru>
object: Miss Coco Peru (born August 27, 1965) is the drag persona of American actor, comedian and drag performer Clinton Leupp, known for her role in the 1999 independent film Trick and for her series of live theater performances. Recognizable by her "trademark copper-toned flip hairdo", Peru also starred in Richard Day's Girls Will Be Girls (2003) and was one of six performers featured in the Logo original stand-up comedy series Wisecrack (2005). She has also appeared in a number of other supporting and guest-starring roles in film and television.

subject: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miss_Coco_Peru>
object: Miss Coco Peru, nombre artístico de Clinton Leupp, es una artista, drag queen estadounidense, más conocido por su papel en la película independiente Trick (1999).​ Peru también protagonizó la película (2003) de , fue uno de los seis actores que protagonizaban la serie de monólogos humorísticos (2005) de Logo y tuvo un cameo en la comedia To Wong Foo, Thanks for Everything! Julie Newmar (1995). Ha aparecido en numerosas series de televisión en papeles secundarios o como estrella invitada, incluyendo Will & Grace, el programa de telerrealidad del canal de televisión estadounidense y la comedia (como la mujer del jefe del estudio S.R.O. que es lesbiana en secreto). En 2009 presentó en directo los 20 premios anuales «GLAAD Media» en el teatro Nokia de Los Ángeles.​

subject: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miss_Coco_Peru>
object: Miss Coco Peru (born August 27, 1965) is the drag persona of American actor, comedian and drag performer Clinton Leupp, known for her role in the 1999 independent film Trick and for her series of live theater performances. Recognizable by her "trademark copper-toned flip hairdo", Peru also starred in Richard Day's Girls Will Be Girls (2003) and was one of six performers featured in the Logo original stand-up comedy series Wisecrack (2005). She has also appeared in a number of other supporting and guest-starring roles in film and television. For 20 years Peru has starred in various "one-woman shows" across the US and other countries, and hosted LGBT events. Since 2005 Peru has appeared in the "Conversations with Coco" series in which she "interviews and celebrates the lives and careers of the LGBT community's favorite icons." Peru's guests have included Bea Arthur, Liza Minnelli, Lesley Ann Warren, Karen Black, Lily Tomlin and Jane Fonda.
